Final Report – IS Project Management Practice
1. Introduction

This project focused on learning and applying basic project management
concepts by using digital collaboration tools. The main goal was to plan,
track, and manage tasks effectively while practicing teamwork. 
The tools used in this project were Trello for task management and GitHub for file sharing and version control.

The project involved creating a task board, assigning responsibilities,
tracking progress, and managing documents through an online repository.

2. Objectives
Organize project activities using digital tools
Assign tasks and manage team responsibilities
Track progress throughout the project lifecycle
Use version control to manage project files
Complete all project deliverables on time
3. Tools Used
3.1 Trello

Trello was used to create a visual workflow for managing project tasks. It helped the team:

Organize tasks into lists (To Do, In Progress, Testing, Completed)
Assign tasks to members
Set deadlines
Track progress visually
Communicate through comments and attachments

This improved task clarity and helped ensure that all work was completed on time.

3.2 GitHub

GitHub was used to store and manage project documents. It provided:

A centralized repository for all project files
Version control to track changes
Collaboration through commits and issues
A structured workflow for updating documents

GitHub ensured that all team members worked with the most up-to-date documents and reduced the risk of file loss.

4. Work Completed

The following tasks were completed during the project:

Defined project scope and objectives
Identified project stakeholders
Created a Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)
Prepared a risk management plan
Developed a project schedule
Tracked tasks and updated progress regularly
Completed and uploaded the final report

All tasks were assigned to specific team members, and progress was monitored regularly using the task board.

5. Benefits of Using These Tools

Using Trello and GitHub provided several benefits:

Improved teamwork and communication
Clear visibility of project tasks and responsibilities
Better time management and organization
Centralized storage and easy access to files
Transparent tracking of progress and contributions

These tools helped the team stay organized and complete the project efficiently.

6. Challenges and Lessons Learned

Some challenges faced during the project included:

Adjusting to new tools at the beginning
Coordinating schedules among team members

Lessons learned:

Early planning and clear communication are essential
Digital tools make project management more efficient
Dividing tasks clearly improves productivity
7. Conclusion

This project demonstrated how digital tools can effectively support project management.
By using Trello for task tracking and GitHub for collaboration and version control,
the team was able to organize tasks, collaborate efficiently, and complete the project successfully. 
The experience improved our understanding of teamwork, planning, and project management practices.
